******
[2]
Date: Tue 16 Nov 2021
From: Ramon Noseda <rnoseda@laboratorioazul.com.ar> [edited]


The province of La Pampa has had repeated outbreaks of bovine anthrax. The Laboratorio Santa Rosa (Dr. Fernando Esain) noted that in the 14 years since 2014 it was an important epidemiologic risk and a constant concern in provincial policy. In the period 2006-2019, they processed 669 suspect samples and 50 were confirmed to be _Bacillus anthracis_ positive.

The province is made up of 22 departments of which 11 (50%) had had outbreaks of livestock anthrax during 2016-2019. These were Atreuco, Capital, Conhelo, Guatrache, Hucal, Lihuel Calel, Loventue, Rancul, Realico, Toay, and Utracan. All are subject to compulsory vaccination in the province.

In 2020, the Santa Rosa laboratory examined 49 suspect samples of which 2 (4%) were positive. At the present time, anthrax is an endemic risk in the provinces of Rio Negro, La Pampa, and Buenos Aires.

--
Communicated by:
Ramon Noseda
